fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with secular authorities the Christian should not only be above </div><div class="t m84a x70 h14 y9f0 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">reproach, but should &quot;be ready to do whatever is good&quot; (verse </div><div class="t m314 x70 h14 y9f2 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1, NIV). </div><div class="t m84b x5c h14 y246 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">When we were living in habitual sin, we were ruled by our </div><div class="t m84c x70 h14 y9f4 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">passions and in constant conflict with our fellow human be-</div><div class="t m113 x70 h14 y9f5 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ings. Then came rebirth and renewal by the inner saving work </div><div class="t m84d x70 h14 y9f6 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of the Holy Spirit. The power to live as God instructs is </div><div class="t m13a x70 h14 ya61 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">provided by the saving grace of Christ bestowed upon us by </div><div class="t m555 x70 h14 y9f8 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the Holy Spirit. Salvation through Christ not only fits us for </div><div class="t m27f x70 h14 ya62 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">worthy citizenship on earth, it makes us &quot;heirs according to </div><div class="t m223 x70 h14 y9f9 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the hope of eternal life&quot; (verse 7). </div><div class="t m84e x5c h14 y96d ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Titus 3 provides one of Scripture&apos;s clearest statements of </div><div class="t m84f x70 h14 y96e ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">salvation by grace resulting in good works. </div><div class="t m1f2 x70 h14 ya63 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">90 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
